The Grand Prix will go ahead.

960
01:05:51,410 --> 01:05:53,094
The race is going ahead.

961
01:05:57,330 --> 01:05:58,569
Niki!

962
01:05:58,570 --> 01:06:00,334
<i>One minute to go.</i>

963
01:06:09,850 --> 01:06:13,049
Jochen's going on slicks.
You wanna change?

964
01:06:13,050 --> 01:06:15,609
- Is Niki gonna change?
- No.

965
01:06:15,610 --> 01:06:17,692
Then we stay on wets, too.

966
01:06:25,530 --> 01:06:27,294
- Niki, okay?
- I'm good.

967
01:06:29,770 --> 01:06:32,250
All right, fire her up.

968
01:06:45,464 --> 01:06:48,249
<i>This season's fight for
the Formula 1 World Championship</i>

969
01:06:48,250 --> 01:06:51,929
<i>has so far been the story of two men.</i>

970
01:06:51,930 --> 01:06:55,609
<i>Thus far, it's been going
pretty much the way of Niki Lauda.</i>

971
01:06:55,610 --> 01:06:58,295
<i>But James Hunt
has qualified fastest here.</i>

972
01:06:58,410 --> 01:07:01,489
<i>He is on pole position
for the German Grand Prix,</i>

973
01:07:01,490 --> 01:07:04,573
<i>with Niki Lauda alongside
in the blood-red Ferrari.</i>

974
01:07:06,010 --> 01:07:07,489
<i>It's a long race.</i>

975
01:07:07,490 --> 01:07:10,141
If the track starts to dry out,

976
01:07:10,250 --> 01:07:13,094
the wet-weather tyres
will no longer be as quick.

977
01:07:34,505 --> 01:07:36,609
Niki Lauda
and James Hunt, side by side

978
01:07:36,610 --> 01:07:39,773
on the front row of the grid,
go away absolutely as one.

979
01:07:53,970 --> 01:07:56,177
<i>Lauda very aggressive on Hunt there,</i>

980
01:07:56,290 --> 01:07:58,292
<i>forcing the McLaren onto the grass.</i>

981
01:08:02,650 --> 01:08:04,129
<i>Lauda has the lead at the moment.</i>

982
01:08:04,130 --> 01:08:06,497
Lauda leads into the first corner.

983
01:08:06,690 --> 01:08:08,658
<i>Hunt is in second place.</i>

984
01:08:13,330 --> 01:08:15,969
<i>Mass storming past Hunt!</i>

985
01:08:15,970 --> 01:08:18,655
<i>He made the right choice
to go with the dry-weather tyres.</i>

986
01:08:20,170 --> 01:08:21,979
<i>Mass passing Lauda now!</i>

987
01:08:22,090 --> 01:08:26,015
<i>Jochen Mass, in the number 12 McLaren,
takes the lead!</i>

988
01:08:26,170 --> 01:08:27,854
Jochen Mass the clear leader,

989
01:08:28,010 --> 01:08:30,058
with everybody else making the decision

990
01:08:30,170 --> 01:08:32,329
to change tyres
after just one lap of this race.

991
01:08:32,330 --> 01:08:34,537
He's coming in! Come on, let's go!

992
01:08:42,690 --> 01:08:46,740
See? I told you to go on slicks.
You should have taken my advice.

993
01:08:46,850 --> 01:08:48,689
Fuck off. Where's Niki?

994
01:08:48,690 --> 01:08:51,375
Behind you.
He made the same mistake.

995
01:09:04,130 --> 01:09:05,859
Come on!

996
01:09:08,410 --> 01:09:10,219
Come on! What's going on?

997
01:09:11,730 --> 01:09:15,089
The tyre-changing frenzy has caused
a huge reshuffling of the pack,

998
01:09:15,090 --> 01:09:18,060
- with Jochen Mass in the lead now.
- You're clear. Go!

999
01:09:18,610 --> 01:09:19,736
Quick!

1000
01:09:21,210 --> 01:09:23,049
Lauda urging his mechanics to hurry.

1001
01:09:23,050 --> 01:09:24,211
Quicker, quicker, quicker!

1002
01:09:25,970 --> 01:09:28,052
It's a disaster! Come on!

1003
01:09:39,610 --> 01:09:41,180
What's going on, you assholes?

1004
01:10:04,930 --> 01:10:07,169
This race has gone wrong for him so far.

1005
01:10:07,170 --> 01:10:10,617
<i>His championship rival, James Hunt,
is a long way up the road.</i>

1006
01:10:21,490 --> 01:10:22,969
<i>Lauda passing car after car.</i>

1007
01:10:22,970 --> 01:10:26,452
<i>He's just going past
Mario Andretti's Lotus there.</i>

1008
01:11:13,170 --> 01:11:15,172
Niki!

1009
01:11:20,170 --> 01:11:22,252
Get me out! Help me!

1010
01:11:22,850 --> 01:11:25,410
<i>We have an accident
on the course. Red flags are out.</i>

1011
01:11:25,690 --> 01:11:29,490
<i>Several cars are involved. Looks like
it might be one of the Ferraris.</i>

1012
01:11:36,690 --> 01:11:39,057
- Come this way.
- Come on, come on!

1013
01:11:51,290 --> 01:11:52,769
Keep trying.

1014
01:12:00,370 --> 01:12:02,010
- Come this way.
- Okay.

1015
01:12:07,747 --> 01:12:14,377
<i>News is reaching us that Niki Lauda
was involved in the accident.</i>

1016
01:12:14,457 --> 01:12:20,427
<i>He is being flown by helicopter
to Mannheim hospital with severe burns.</i>

1017
01:12:53,930 --> 01:12:57,980
<i>It's not
the burns to his face that are the danger.</i>

1018
01:12:59,047 --> 01:13:01,047
<i>It's the burns to his lungs.</i>

1019
01:13:03,797 --> 01:13:06,025
In the
intensive care unit,

1020
01:13:06,025 --> 01:13:09,081
six doctors and thirty-four
nurses are on duty for him.

1021
01:13:10,267 --> 01:13:13,557
But his condition is far worse
than originally feared.

1022
01:13:40,290 --> 01:13:43,809
<i>The flood, which swept
down Big Thompson Canyon in Colorado,</i>

1023
01:13:43,810 --> 01:13:45,529
<i>was the worst since records began.</i>

1024
01:13:45,530 --> 01:13:48,129
<i>In Formula 1 today,
victory celebrations were muted</i>

1025
01:13:48,130 --> 01:13:51,969
<i>after a horrific accident involving
world champion Niki Lauda.</i>

1026
01:13:51,970 --> 01:13:53,969
<i>Due to safety concerns before the race,</i>

1027
01:13:53,970 --> 01:13:56,369
<i>the Austrian had said
he would not take part,</i>

1028
01:13:56,370 --> 01:13:57,860
<i>but in the end he did.</i>

1029
01:13:59,250 --> 01:14:01,537
<i>He was making up for lost time
when he went off the track,</i>

1030
01:14:01,650 --> 01:14:04,017
<i>puncturing the Ferrari's fuel tank.</i>

1031
01:14:04,410 --> 01:14:06,697
<i>Brett Lunger was unable to
avoid the flaming wreck,</i>

1032
01:14:06,850 --> 01:14:09,849
<i>but was unhurt and joined with
the other drivers to rescue Lauda,</i>

1033
01:14:09,850 --> 01:14:12,740
<i>who was taken to Mannheim Hospital
with severe burns,</i>

1034
01:14:12,850 --> 01:14:16,491
<i>the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.</i>

1035
01:14:16,610 --> 01:14:18,689
<i>Niki Lauda was trapped
for almost a minute</i>

1036
01:14:18,690 --> 01:14:21,341
<i>in a searing inferno
of 800-plus degrees.</i>

1037
01:14:30,170 --> 01:14:32,449
- Do we have any change this morning?
- No...

1038
01:14:32,450 --> 01:14:34,373
<i>Frau</i> Lauda. <i>Frau</i> Lauda?

1039
01:14:35,210 --> 01:14:37,372
He's awake and just spoke.

1040
01:14:38,977 --> 01:14:42,567
He said, "Tell the priest to fuck off!
I'm still alive!"

1041
01:14:42,737 --> 01:14:44,397
You can go in.

1042
01:16:06,147 --> 01:16:10,737
<i>James Hunt gains on the absent Niki Lauda.</i>

1043
01:16:17,907 --> 01:16:19,977
<i>We need to vacuum the lungs.</i>

1044
01:16:20,756 --> 01:16:23,450
<i>I should warn you. It won't be easy.</i>

1045
01:17:32,527 --> 01:17:33,907
Do it again.

1046
01:17:34,157 --> 01:17:38,311
Are you sure?
The lungs will already be bruised.

1047
01:18:09,330 --> 01:18:11,094
- Niki...

1048
01:18:20,237 --> 01:18:22,327
Please, stop.

1049
01:18:23,327 --> 01:18:26,877
I know what you're thinking,
but please...

1050
01:18:28,207 --> 01:18:31,507
If you love me, you won't say a word.

1051
01:19:08,130 --> 01:19:10,019
- Morning, chaps.
- Hey, here's the man.

1052
01:19:10,210 --> 01:19:11,860
Looking good.

1053
01:19:15,090 --> 01:19:17,969
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

1054
01:19:17,970 --> 01:19:20,018
- What about him?
- He's here.

1055
01:19:20,330 --> 01:19:21,855
- What?
- He's racing.

1056
01:19:37,210 --> 01:19:38,860
Niki.

1057
01:19:45,490 --> 01:19:47,015
It's that bad, huh?

1058
01:19:48,330 --> 01:19:49,741
No.

1059
01:19:50,610 --> 01:19:53,609
In hospital I asked them straight,
no bullshit,

1060
01:19:53,610 --> 01:19:55,453
how bad my appearance would be.

1061
01:19:56,690 --> 01:19:59,057
They said with time it would be fine.

1062
01:19:59,930 --> 01:20:01,534
But it won't.

1063
01:20:02,450 --> 01:20:05,294
I can tell, seeing your reaction.

1064
01:20:06,250 --> 01:20:09,254
I will spend the rest of my life
with a face that frightens people.

1065
01:20:13,370 --> 01:20:17,136
You know, Niki, I tried to write you
a letter at the time, to apologise.

1066
01:20:18,770 --> 01:20:21,250
The drivers' meeting in Germany,
before the race.

1067
01:20:21,370 --> 01:20:23,896
- I swayed the room.
- Yes, you did.

1068
01:20:24,090 --> 01:20:26,297
That race should never have gone ahead.

1069
01:20:27,050 --> 01:20:28,654
No, it shouldn't.

1070
01:20:29,090 --> 01:20:32,809
So, in many ways, I feel responsible
for what happened, and...

1071
01:20:32,810 --> 01:20:34,380
You were.

1072
01:20:36,050 --> 01:20:37,779
But, trust me...

1073
01:20:38,930 --> 01:20:42,980
watching you win those races
while I was fighting for my life...

1074
01:20:45,290 --> 01:20:48,499
...you were equally responsible
for getting me back in the car.

1075
01:21:16,250 --> 01:21:18,935
- How are you feeling, Niki?
- Fine.

1076
01:21:19,330 --> 01:21:22,969
Niki, can you confirm to us exactly
which procedures you've had

1077
01:21:22,970 --> 01:21:24,972
and the expectations for your recovery?

1078
01:21:25,530 --> 01:21:26,975
Sure.

1079
01:21:27,130 --> 01:21:28,969
I had a skin graft operation,

1080
01:21:28,970 --> 01:21:31,291
where they put half my right thigh
in my face.

1081
01:21:33,490 --> 01:21:38,329
Now, it doesn't look too good,
but one unexpected advantage is

1082
01:21:38,330 --> 01:21:40,689
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft,

1083
01:21:40,690 --> 01:21:44,129
so sweat will never run into my eyes
again, which is good for a driver.

1084
01:21:46,330 --> 01:21:48,009
When they heard about your condition,

1085
01:21:48,010 --> 01:21:51,457
Ferrari immediately hired
a replacement driver, Carlos Reutemann.

1086
01:21:52,130 --> 01:21:56,169
Yeah, before even reaching the hospital.

1087
01:21:56,170 --> 01:21:58,218
Is Reutemann
driving today, too?

1088
01:21:58,650 --> 01:22:01,654
Yes, and keen to make an impression.

1089
01:22:01,850 --> 01:22:05,849
So, let's see where Mr Reutemann
finishes and where I finish today.

1090
01:22:07,370 --> 01:22:10,055
James Hunt and McLaren have
caught up a lot while you were away.

1091
01:22:10,690 --> 01:22:12,180
Yes.

1092
01:22:12,810 --> 01:22:15,809
So is there a question now,
or are you just trying to piss me off?

1093
01:22:19,090 --> 01:22:20,819
You still think you can win?

1094
01:22:21,250 --> 01:22:23,049
Yes, of course.

1095
01:22:23,050 --> 01:22:25,052
I have the better car.

1096
01:22:25,170 --> 01:22:27,650
And possibly I'm the better driver.

1097
01:22:27,850 --> 01:22:30,329
But he's a clever guy,
and he's used his time well

1098
01:22:30,330 --> 01:22:34,380
while I was lying half-dead in hospital
to win some points.

1099
01:22:36,330 --> 01:22:39,015
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1100
01:22:45,210 --> 01:22:48,769
She said, "Sweetie,
you don't need a face to drive."

1101
01:22:48,770 --> 01:22:50,898
"You just need a right foot."

1102
01:22:51,210 --> 01:22:53,577
I'm being serious.

1103
01:22:53,770 --> 01:22:58,253
Do you really think your marriage can
survive with the way you look now?

1104
01:23:00,890 --> 01:23:02,938
And I'm being serious, too.

1105
01:23:03,930 --> 01:23:06,900
Fuck you. Press conference over.

1106
01:23:11,585 --> 01:23:13,929
- That was hairy.
- Well, you got noticed, Clive.

1107
01:23:13,930 --> 01:23:15,289
I'll tell you that.

1108
01:23:15,290 --> 01:23:16,969
I thought it went well,
to be honest.

1109
01:23:16,970 --> 01:23:18,769
They don't like it
when it's not going their way.

1110
01:23:18,770 --> 01:23:20,454
- Clive.
- That's the game.

1111
01:23:20,570 --> 01:23:22,889
- See you.
- See you later.

1112
01:23:22,890 --> 01:23:24,779
- James, are you all right?
- Good, yeah.

1113
01:23:24,890 --> 01:23:26,649
Listen, I think
I've got something for you

1114
01:23:26,650 --> 01:23:28,449
on that last question, about Niki.

1115
01:23:28,450 --> 01:23:31,056
You heard about that?
I did.

1116
01:23:32,290 --> 01:23:34,019
James.

1117
01:23:40,250 --> 01:23:42,821
Please, James...

1118
01:23:43,810 --> 01:23:46,734
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1119
01:23:49,170 --> 01:23:50,581
Prick.

1120
01:24:07,450 --> 01:24:12,331
So Niki Lauda, just 42 days after
his near-fatal accident at Nürburgring,

1121
01:24:12,450 --> 01:24:14,009
will race here today at Monza

1122
01:24:14,010 --> 01:24:17,776
against all medical advice
and no doubt in incredible pain.

1123
01:24:50,490 --> 01:24:52,209
<i>...Niki Lauda!</i>

1124
01:25:00,850 --> 01:25:03,251
<i>Photographers,
please clear the grid.</i>

1125
01:25:03,490 --> 01:25:05,652
Niki, it's time.

1126
01:25:07,170 --> 01:25:08,660
Okay?

1127
01:25:15,330 --> 01:25:16,741
<i>Please clear the grid.</i>

1128
01:25:19,370 --> 01:25:21,498
<i>One minute to go.</i>

1129
01:25:58,827 --> 01:26:02,537
That's a bad start for Lauda,
he's slow away.

1130
01:26:07,290 --> 01:26:10,209
<i>The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.</i>

1131
01:26:10,210 --> 01:26:12,656
<i>He's being overtaken by car after car.</i>

1132
01:26:15,490 --> 01:26:17,217
A terrible start for the Austrian.

1133
01:26:17,217 --> 01:26:19,557
<i>It's perhaps too soon for him
to be racing again.</i>

1134
01:26:22,450 --> 01:26:25,579
<i>Lauda's off line.
He runs wide onto the grass.</i>

1135
01:26:30,410 --> 01:26:32,094
<i>He wrestles it back onto the track,</i>

1136
01:26:32,290 --> 01:26:35,100
<i>but that was a bad moment for Niki.</i>

1137
01:26:38,970 --> 01:26:41,249
<i>Niki Lauda's the reigning
world champion,</i>

1138
01:26:41,250 --> 01:26:44,459
<i>but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there,</i>

1139
01:26:44,610 --> 01:26:47,420
<i>to himself and to the rest of the field.</i>

1140
01:26:49,410 --> 01:26:53,301
<i>And Stuck has collided
with Mario Andretti's Lotus!</i>

1141
01:26:53,450 --> 01:26:56,613
<i>Niki's boxed in. He's got nowhere to go.</i>

1142
01:27:11,050 --> 01:27:14,611
<i>Niki Lauda is actually
making a move. He's on Brambilla's tail.</i>

1143
01:27:17,890 --> 01:27:20,541
<i>He pulls out of the slipstream
to overtake.</i>

1144
01:27:21,290 --> 01:27:23,611
<i>Lauda's starting to find the form</i>

1145
01:27:23,730 --> 01:27:25,698
<i>that, early in this race,
we believed he'd lost.</i>

1146
01:27:32,130 --> 01:27:36,215
Lauda's now lapping faster than
Reutemann and closing the gap ahead.

1147
01:27:40,130 --> 01:27:42,701
<i>Lauda closing on Carlos Reutemann,</i>

1148
01:27:42,810 --> 01:27:45,973
<i>the man called in to be his replacement
in the Ferrari team.</i>

1149
01:27:55,010 --> 01:27:56,819
<i>And there's James Hunt's McLaren,</i>

1150
01:27:56,930 --> 01:27:59,376
<i>smoking stationary
by the side of the road.</i>

1151
01:28:03,010 --> 01:28:06,093
<i>This is bad news for Hunt's
championship hopes.</i>

1152
01:28:10,490 --> 01:28:11,901
<i>It's Ronnie Peterson</i>

1153
01:28:12,010 --> 01:28:14,377
<i>who comes home the winner here at Monza.</i>

1154
01:28:14,570 --> 01:28:17,460
<i>But all eyes are on the man
who finishes a brilliant fourth,</i>

1155
01:28:18,410 --> 01:28:20,538
<i>Niki Lauda!</i>

1156
01:29:01,410 --> 01:29:03,809
<i>What a race, what a man,
what a season.</i>

1157
01:29:03,810 --> 01:29:06,049
With a fourth-place finish
and three priceless points,

1158
01:29:06,050 --> 01:29:08,089
it means that Niki Lauda
is a major step closer

1159
01:29:08,090 --> 01:29:10,297
to retaining the World Championship.

1160
01:30:09,450 --> 01:30:13,009
<i>So, the long, gruelling
and incredibly dramatic season</i>

1161
01:30:13,010 --> 01:30:15,449
<i>comes down to this final race in Japan</i>

1162
01:30:15,450 --> 01:30:18,049
<i>in the shadow of Mount Fuji.</i>

1163
01:30:18,050 --> 01:30:19,529
<i>Niki Lauda goes into</i>

1164
01:30:19,530 --> 01:30:21,049
<i>this deciding race at Fuji</i>

1165
01:30:21,050 --> 01:30:23,289
<i>just three points ahead of James Hunt.</i>

1166
01:30:23,290 --> 01:30:27,579
<i>Hunt knowing he must beat the Austrian
fair and square to take the title.</i>

1167
01:30:29,130 --> 01:30:32,689
James, do you think
you can cope with the pressure?

1168
01:30:32,690 --> 01:30:36,217
Well, I've never really understood
what that means. I love my job.

1169
01:30:36,330 --> 01:30:38,378
I love competing. I love racing.

1170
01:30:38,570 --> 01:30:40,489
<i>Maybe you should ask Niki.</i>

1171
01:30:40,490 --> 01:30:42,849
He's the World Champion.
He's got everything to lose.

1172
01:30:42,850 --> 01:30:45,249
Mr Lauda,
are you feeling pressure?

1173
01:30:45,250 --> 01:30:47,696
Do I look like I'm feeling pressure?

1174
01:30:49,770 --> 01:30:53,900
I am World Champion, and on the verge
to become World Champion again.

1175
01:30:54,010 --> 01:30:56,089
Hunt now has the opportunity to win,

1176
01:30:56,090 --> 01:30:58,249
but it's not so easy
to become a champion.

1177
01:30:58,250 --> 01:31:01,379
You have to really believe it
to make it possible.

1178
01:31:01,530 --> 01:31:03,578
James, is there anything
you'd like to add?

1179
01:31:03,690 --> 01:31:07,689
If Niki is being tricky and getting
a kicky out of playing mind games...

1180
01:31:07,690 --> 01:31:10,057
...then fine, I'm flattered.

1181
01:31:10,170 --> 01:31:13,731
But the fact is, momentum is with me.
I've never felt better.

1182
01:31:13,850 --> 01:31:16,421
And I fully expect the next
press conference we will have

1183
01:31:16,530 --> 01:31:18,692
will be with me as World Champion.

1184
01:31:20,530 --> 01:31:23,049
How will you cope
with the weather, bad conditions?

1185
01:31:23,050 --> 01:31:26,609
Intermittent heavy rain
has been forecast here at Fuji today,

1186
01:31:26,610 --> 01:31:30,092
along with strong winds
and occasional fog

1187
01:31:30,210 --> 01:31:32,099
rolling in from the mountain.

1188
01:31:33,890 --> 01:31:36,609
<i>And so, with today's
Japanese Grand Prix to come,</i>

1189
01:31:36,610 --> 01:31:38,449
<i>Lauda's lead a mere three points.</i>

1190
01:31:38,450 --> 01:31:40,134
<i>What a way to finish the season.</i>

1191
01:31:40,730 --> 01:31:42,289
<i>Hunt or Lauda?</i>

1192
01:31:42,290 --> 01:31:45,294
<i>Well, the final chapter will unfold when
we bring you extended coverage...</i>

1193
01:31:45,410 --> 01:31:48,529
They've got to cancel the race.
It's lethal out there.

1194
01:31:48,530 --> 01:31:50,729
The race is going ahead.

1195
01:31:50,730 --> 01:31:52,649
Television rights have been sold
all around the world.

1196
01:31:52,650 --> 01:31:55,369
The showdown between you and Niki
is all anyone wants to see.

1197
01:31:55,370 --> 01:31:58,849
With heavy rain
continuing to fall here at Fuji,

1198
01:31:58,850 --> 01:32:00,932
a decision has finally been made.

1199
01:32:01,050 --> 01:32:05,049
The 1976 Japanese Grand Prix
will go ahead.

1200
01:32:05,050 --> 01:32:07,735
<i>All drivers
to your cars, please.</i>

1201
01:32:32,370 --> 01:32:33,781
<i>Five minutes to go.</i>

1202
01:33:16,970 --> 01:33:18,489
- All right?
- All right.

1203
01:33:18,490 --> 01:33:20,889
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1204
01:33:20,890 --> 01:33:22,689
To let the condensation out.

1205
01:33:22,690 --> 01:33:25,489
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1206
01:33:25,490 --> 01:33:27,857
Trust me,
this race is all about the start.

1207
01:33:29,770 --> 01:33:32,341
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah, hold it, Teddy.

1208
01:33:46,810 --> 01:33:48,460
Okay, start the bastard.

1209
01:33:51,450 --> 01:33:53,100
Good luck, kid.

1210
01:33:54,490 --> 01:33:55,901
Good luck, James.

1211
01:34:35,450 --> 01:34:37,452
<i>Thirty seconds to go.</i>

1212
01:34:56,890 --> 01:34:59,129
<i>Electric tension here at Fuji.</i>

1213
01:34:59,130 --> 01:35:04,249
<i>80, 000 bedraggled race fans and
the racing grudge match of the decade.</i>

1214
01:35:04,250 --> 01:35:06,449
<i>And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position,</i>

1215
01:35:06,450 --> 01:35:08,452
<i>James Hunt alongside him.</i>

1216
01:35:10,610 --> 01:35:12,609
<i>On Row 2 of the grid,</i>

1217
01:35:12,610 --> 01:35:14,569
<i>there is Niki Lauda,</i>

1218
01:35:14,570 --> 01:35:17,089
<i>and on Row 3 of the grid,
Jody Scheckter from South Africa</i>

1219
01:35:17,090 --> 01:35:18,609
<i>in the six-wheel Tyrrell.</i>

1220
01:35:18,610 --> 01:35:20,692
<i>Behind him,
the rest of the 25-car field.</i>

1221
01:35:38,530 --> 01:35:42,535
There's the flag, and finally
the Japanese Grand Prix is underway!

1222
01:35:54,770 --> 01:35:58,009
<i>In these conditions,
it must be almost impossible to drive</i>

1223
01:35:58,010 --> 01:36:00,012
<i>a 450-horsepower car.</i>

1224
01:36:27,170 --> 01:36:30,249
<i>And it's Andretti who has the lead,
but Hunt is attacking.</i>

1225
01:36:30,250 --> 01:36:33,289
<i>Hunt's going round
the outside of Andretti.</i>

1226
01:36:33,290 --> 01:36:34,929
<i>Niki Lauda following him through.</i>

1227
01:36:34,930 --> 01:36:37,695
<i>Hunt leads into the first right-hander.</i>

1228
01:37:20,225 --> 01:37:22,569
<i>Hunt comes through
to complete his first lap,</i>

1229
01:37:22,570 --> 01:37:24,049
<i>leading the field.</i>

1230
01:37:24,050 --> 01:37:26,178
<i>At least he has clear vision
in front of him.</i>

1231
01:37:26,290 --> 01:37:28,452
<i>Niki Lauda, behind him,
eating his spray.</i>

1232
01:37:47,930 --> 01:37:49,409
<i>Lauda is slowing.</i>

1233
01:37:49,410 --> 01:37:52,369
<i>Niki Lauda is bringing
the Ferrari number one into the pit.</i>

1234
01:37:54,050 --> 01:37:57,259
<i>Some sort of problem, we can't
imagine what, so early in the race.</i>

1235
01:38:03,570 --> 01:38:07,017
What's wrong with the car?
What's wrong with the car?

1236
01:38:08,170 --> 01:38:09,899
Niki, what's wrong with the car?

1237
01:38:10,250 --> 01:38:12,332
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1238
01:38:16,730 --> 01:38:19,169
- What are you doing?
- I'm stopping.

1239
01:38:19,170 --> 01:38:21,409
<i>His mechanics
are asking what the problem is.</i>

1240
01:38:21,410 --> 01:38:23,731
<i>But wait!
Niki Lauda's getting out of the car!</i>

1241
01:38:23,850 --> 01:38:25,529
This is sensational!

1242
01:38:25,530 --> 01:38:28,454
The reigning World Champion,
Niki Lauda, is out of this race.

1243
01:38:29,370 --> 01:38:31,129
It's too dangerous.

1244
01:38:31,130 --> 01:38:34,339
Niki, you want me to say there was
a problem with the car, for the media?

1245
01:38:35,650 --> 01:38:37,140
No.

1246
01:38:37,530 --> 01:38:38,941
Tell them the truth.

1247
01:38:39,810 --> 01:38:41,380
<i>Now, what is happening?</i>

1248
01:38:41,490 --> 01:38:45,415
<i>They're talking to the team manager.
Lauda explaining something.</i>

1249
01:39:00,970 --> 01:39:04,329
<i>With Lauda out, James Hunt
knows he has to finish this race</i>

1250
01:39:04,330 --> 01:39:08,169
<i>in third place or higher
to be World Champion.</i>

1251
01:39:08,170 --> 01:39:10,929
<i>But the job's not done yet
for James Hunt.</i>

1252
01:39:10,930 --> 01:39:15,538
<i>In these dreadful conditions,
he still has to go the distance.</i>

1253
01:39:16,650 --> 01:39:18,493
<i>Fifteen laps to go here at Fuji.</i>

1254
01:39:18,610 --> 01:39:20,769
<i>James Hunt or Niki Lauda?</i>

1255
01:39:20,770 --> 01:39:23,929
<i>This extraordinary season
is not over yet.</i>

1256
01:39:23,930 --> 01:39:27,377
<i>In this treacherous final round,
can James Hunt hang on?</i>

1257
01:39:27,890 --> 01:39:29,809
<i>And the scoreboard tells a story.</i>

1258
01:39:29,810 --> 01:39:32,620
<i>Lap 58. Hunt in the lead.</i>

1259
01:39:34,610 --> 01:39:36,453
Oh, God, his tyres, they're blistering.

1260
01:39:37,865 --> 01:39:39,929
<i>Brambilla
very close behind now,</i>

1261
01:39:39,930 --> 01:39:41,898
<i>closing on him all the time now.</i>

1262
01:39:42,010 --> 01:39:45,249
<i>And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.</i>

1263
01:39:45,250 --> 01:39:47,776
<i>Hunt cuts across the orange March nose.</i>

1264
01:39:47,890 --> 01:39:50,249
<i>Hunt's not having that at all.
And he's spinning.</i>

1265
01:39:50,250 --> 01:39:53,489
<i>He missed Hunt there, but almost
took James Hunt out of the race</i>

1266
01:39:53,490 --> 01:39:55,929
<i>and out of the world championship.</i>

1267
01:39:55,930 --> 01:39:58,661
<i>Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.</i>

1268
01:40:03,210 --> 01:40:05,178
<i>Mario Andretti's going past Hunt!</i>

1269
01:40:05,650 --> 01:40:08,654
<i>Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a problem.</i>

1270
01:40:14,490 --> 01:40:16,329
<i>Despite these wet conditions,</i>

1271
01:40:16,330 --> 01:40:18,059
<i>these wet-weather tyres
do wear extremely fast.</i>

1272
01:40:18,170 --> 01:40:20,298
Hunt's tyres, they've gone.

1273
01:40:20,530 --> 01:40:24,216
<i>Hunt nursing his car
back to the pit stop.</i>

1274
01:40:26,210 --> 01:40:28,258
<i>That back marker's going past Hunt.</i>

1275
01:40:40,690 --> 01:40:43,449
<i>Look at that left front tyre...
Right front tyre, sorry.</i>

1276
01:40:43,450 --> 01:40:46,613
<i>No tread on it at all.
And the other one is flat.</i>

1277
01:40:46,770 --> 01:40:48,898
Let's go! Let's go!

1278
01:40:53,450 --> 01:40:55,929
Okay? When did you break
your gear lever?

1279
01:40:55,930 --> 01:40:57,609
Nine or ten laps ago.

1280
01:40:57,610 --> 01:41:00,056
- Alastair, we need to lift it.
- Come on!

1281
01:41:00,170 --> 01:41:01,929
- At the front.
- Let's go.

1282
01:41:01,930 --> 01:41:05,209
<i>Regazzoni's Ferrari
and Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier</i>

1283
01:41:05,210 --> 01:41:06,860
have gone ahead.

1284
01:41:06,970 --> 01:41:08,649
Come on, hurry!

1285
01:41:08,650 --> 01:41:11,769
You did it.
You're going to be World Champion!

1286
01:41:11,770 --> 01:41:13,289
Not yet.

1287
01:41:13,290 --> 01:41:17,129
<i>A few laps ago, James Hunt
was looking like champion elect.</i>

1288
01:41:17,130 --> 01:41:19,497
<i>Now it looks as though
it's all gone wrong for him.</i>

1289
01:41:20,930 --> 01:41:22,409
- James.
- Come on!

1290
01:41:22,410 --> 01:41:23,929
- Listen.
- What?

1291
01:41:23,930 --> 01:41:26,249
Just go easy out there.

1292
01:41:26,250 --> 01:41:30,289
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1293
01:41:30,290 --> 01:41:32,249
We want you back in one piece.

1294
01:41:32,250 --> 01:41:35,689
You're too far back. There's
too many drivers in front of you.

1295
01:41:35,690 --> 01:41:39,695
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1296
01:41:40,090 --> 01:41:41,649
Clear!

1297
01:41:41,650 --> 01:41:43,175
James.

1298
01:41:44,850 --> 01:41:46,773
- Clear!
- Fuck it!

1299
01:41:50,690 --> 01:41:54,009
James Hunt rejoins the race
in sixth position.

1300
01:41:54,010 --> 01:41:57,901
<i>There are four laps left to go.
Surely no way back for the Brit now.</i>

1301
01:42:17,770 --> 01:42:19,104
Concentrate, Superstar.

1302
01:42:19,105 --> 01:42:21,009
<i>Just brings
it back under control.</i>

1303
01:42:21,010 --> 01:42:22,289
<i>Sliding the McLaren</i>

1304
01:42:22,290 --> 01:42:23,530
<i>on the very edge there.</i>

1305
01:42:25,450 --> 01:42:26,736
<i>Hunt's M23</i>

1306
01:42:26,850 --> 01:42:28,529
<i>twitching this way and that
under braking.</i>

1307
01:42:28,530 --> 01:42:29,930
And he almost loses it right there.

1308
01:42:30,050 --> 01:42:32,771
<i>Hunt on the tail
of Jacques Lafitte in the blue Ligier.</i>

1309
01:42:40,730 --> 01:42:42,141
Oh, don't do it, James.

1310
01:42:45,265 --> 01:42:47,209
<i>He's inches away
from the pit wall.</i>

1311
01:42:47,210 --> 01:42:49,019
<i>He's inches away from the Ligier.</i>

1312
01:42:58,050 --> 01:43:00,529
<i>James Hunt has made up another place,</i>

1313
01:43:00,530 --> 01:43:01,609
<i>but it's not enough,</i>

1314
01:43:01,610 --> 01:43:02,850
<i>and this race is running out.</i>

1315
01:43:11,890 --> 01:43:13,892
<i>And Watson has spun.
Watson has spun.</i>

1316
01:43:18,530 --> 01:43:21,369
<i>Hunt manages to weave his way
between that back marker</i>

1317
01:43:21,370 --> 01:43:23,449
<i>and the stationary Penske.</i>

1318
01:43:23,450 --> 01:43:25,529
He's catching Regazzoni

1319
01:43:25,530 --> 01:43:27,249
but, in these conditions,
it's one thing to catch up,

1320
01:43:27,250 --> 01:43:29,457
it's quite another to overtake.

1321
01:43:32,850 --> 01:43:36,980
<i>He's alongside Clay Regazzoni.
This could be the world championship.</i>

1322
01:43:45,410 --> 01:43:46,935
<i>He's got him!</i>

1323
01:43:47,397 --> 01:43:50,437
The scoreboard
still shows Hunt in 5th place.

1324
01:44:02,210 --> 01:44:04,369
<i>Hunt crosses the line.</i>

1325
01:44:04,370 --> 01:44:08,049
<i>Now, he needed to finish third to score
enough points to be World Champion,</i>

1326
01:44:08,050 --> 01:44:12,649
<i>and in the confusion here, we're being
told that he may have finished fifth.</i>

1327
01:44:12,650 --> 01:44:14,849
He finished fifth?

1328
01:44:14,850 --> 01:44:17,729
<i>Our lap charts
show Hunt in third place.</i>

1329
01:44:17,730 --> 01:44:19,729
<i>Well, if the scoreboard's right,</i>

1330
01:44:19,730 --> 01:44:22,329
<i>it means he's just missed out
on the championship.</i>

1331
01:44:22,330 --> 01:44:25,971
<i>Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a heroic drive.</i>

1332
01:44:29,930 --> 01:44:32,529
I can see the race stewards conferring,

1333
01:44:32,530 --> 01:44:34,249
examining the official lap charts.

1334
01:44:34,250 --> 01:44:36,651
<i>We're just going to have to wait
for their verdict here.</i>

1335
01:44:54,265 --> 01:44:55,929
Let's get you out of there, buddy.

1336
01:44:55,930 --> 01:44:58,089
I'm sorry, Teddy. I'm sorry.
I thought I could make up the ground.

1337
01:44:58,090 --> 01:45:00,249
Sorry? What are you talking about?
You did it.

1338
01:45:00,250 --> 01:45:03,089
- Did what?
- Jesus. You crazy bastard.

1339
01:45:03,090 --> 01:45:06,299
You came third. You got the points.
You're champion of the world!

1340
01:45:06,810 --> 01:45:10,053
<i>James Hunt
is now officially confirmed</i>

1341
01:45:10,170 --> 01:45:12,218
<i>as finishing third here in Japan,</i>

1342
01:45:12,850 --> 01:45:16,569
<i>and that means
he is champion of the world.</i>

1343
01:45:17,970 --> 01:45:23,329
<i>Our new World Champion,
James Hunt, by just one single point.</i>

1344
01:45:28,450 --> 01:45:29,940
<i>Did we really win?</i>

1345
01:45:34,010 --> 01:45:36,251
World bloody Champion!

1346
01:45:44,945 --> 01:45:47,009
Tell us, James,
what are you going to do now?

1347
01:45:47,010 --> 01:45:49,172
I shall be getting drunk.

1348
01:45:49,690 --> 01:45:52,489
It's wonderful,
an absolute dream...

1349
01:46:05,570 --> 01:46:07,254
Are you okay?

1350
01:46:09,367 --> 01:46:10,957
Fine.

1351
01:46:12,577 --> 01:46:14,327
No regrets.

1352
01:46:17,587 --> 01:46:19,417
Not one.

1353
01:46:39,410 --> 01:46:41,489
<i>And our special guest,</i>

1354
01:46:41,490 --> 01:46:43,333
<i>Formula 1 champion James Hunt.</i>

1355
01:47:06,730 --> 01:47:08,812
Wait. Come on.

1356
01:47:11,970 --> 01:47:13,529
<i>There's no better motor oil</i>

1357
01:47:13,530 --> 01:47:15,134
<i>than Havoline.</i>

1358
01:47:25,650 --> 01:47:27,649
Yes, me, too.
Where are we going?

1359
01:47:27,650 --> 01:47:29,184
Anywhere I want to go.

1360
01:47:29,185 --> 01:47:31,529
And I don't have to hijack it, either.

1361
01:47:31,530 --> 01:47:33,249
As long as I pay for it.

1362
01:47:33,250 --> 01:47:35,571
I'm starving.
Let's get some food.

1363
01:47:46,385 --> 01:47:48,489
- Where are we going?
- You lot go ahead.

1364
01:47:48,490 --> 01:47:50,458
I won't be a minute.

1365
01:47:56,370 --> 01:47:57,974
Good to see you.

1366
01:48:02,050 --> 01:48:04,451
I heard you were spending
more and more time in one of these.

1367
01:48:04,850 --> 01:48:06,818
Do you fly?
No.

1368
01:48:07,210 --> 01:48:08,700
I don't think they'd insure me.

1369
01:48:08,850 --> 01:48:10,693
You should try.
It's good for discipline.

1370
01:48:10,890 --> 01:48:13,370
You have to stay within the rules,
stick to regulations,

1371
01:48:13,490 --> 01:48:16,061
suppress the ego.
It helps with the racing.

1372
01:48:16,170 --> 01:48:19,209
And there I was thinking
you were about to wax lyrical

1373
01:48:19,210 --> 01:48:20,814
about the romance of flight.

1374
01:48:21,170 --> 01:48:22,740
No, that's all bullshit.

1375
01:48:23,890 --> 01:48:25,335
So, what brings you here?

1376
01:48:26,490 --> 01:48:29,049
A friend's wedding.
At least I think it was a wedding.

1377
01:48:29,050 --> 01:48:31,969
Might have been a birthday or something.
It's all a bit of a blur.

1378
01:48:31,970 --> 01:48:33,289
How about you? Have you been at Fiorano?

1379
01:48:33,290 --> 01:48:34,451
Pre-season testing.

1380
01:48:34,570 --> 01:48:36,569
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1381
01:48:36,570 --> 01:48:38,809
I'm not sure that was meant
as a compliment.

1382
01:48:38,810 --> 01:48:41,129
When do you start testing? Next week?

1383
01:48:41,130 --> 01:48:43,169
No. What, are you nuts?

1384
01:48:43,170 --> 01:48:44,969
I didn't just win
the biggest thing of my life

1385
01:48:44,970 --> 01:48:46,415
so I could get right back to work.

1386
01:48:47,730 --> 01:48:50,415
Why? You have to.

1387
01:48:50,730 --> 01:48:54,169
To prove to all the people who will
always say you just won it because...

1388
01:48:54,170 --> 01:48:57,572
Because of what?
Because of your accident?

1389
01:48:59,090 --> 01:49:01,138
Niki, is that other people,
or is that you?

1390
01:49:01,770 --> 01:49:04,929
I won, okay? On the all-important day,
when it came down to it,

1391
01:49:04,930 --> 01:49:07,849
we raced on equal terms,
equally good cars.

1392
01:49:07,850 --> 01:49:10,089
And I put my life on the line,
and I saw it through.

1393
01:49:10,090 --> 01:49:12,138
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1394
01:49:12,250 --> 01:49:14,332
The risks were totally unacceptable.

1395
01:49:14,850 --> 01:49:17,330
You were prepared to die.
To me, that's losing.

1396
01:49:17,450 --> 01:49:19,089
Yes, I was. I admit it.

1397
01:49:19,090 --> 01:49:21,969
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1398
01:49:21,970 --> 01:49:24,940
And that's the effect you have on me.
You'd pushed me that far.

1399
01:49:25,050 --> 01:49:26,461
And it felt great.

1400
01:49:27,370 --> 01:49:29,769
I mean, hell,
isn't that what we're in this for?

1401
01:49:29,770 --> 01:49:33,138
To stare death in the face
and to cheat it?

1402
01:49:33,490 --> 01:49:37,290
Come on, there's nobility in that.
It's... It's like being knights.

1403
01:49:38,290 --> 01:49:40,054
You English, you're such assholes.

1404
01:49:41,010 --> 01:49:42,455
You know my position.

1405
01:49:42,730 --> 01:49:44,209
Twenty per cent risk.

1406
01:49:44,210 --> 01:49:48,009
No, no, no, Niki, don't bring the
percentages into this. Don't be a pro.

1407
01:49:48,010 --> 01:49:50,661
The minute you do that,
you kill what's good about this.

1408
01:49:50,970 --> 01:49:52,734
You kill the sport.

1409
01:49:55,850 --> 01:49:57,500
James!

1410
01:49:57,810 --> 01:49:59,653
- James!
- Come on!

1411
01:50:02,650 --> 01:50:04,015
I've got to go.

1412
01:50:05,530 --> 01:50:07,498
Careful in this thing.

1413
01:50:08,530 --> 01:50:10,020
James.

1414
01:50:15,250 --> 01:50:19,016
You know, in hospital, the toughest part
of my treatment was the vacuum.

1415
01:50:19,330 --> 01:50:22,254
Pumping the shit out of my lungs.
It was hell.

1416
01:50:23,330 --> 01:50:25,253
And while doing it,
I was watching television.

1417
01:50:25,850 --> 01:50:28,689
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1418
01:50:28,690 --> 01:50:30,897
"That bastard Hunt," I would say.
"I hate that guy."

1419
01:50:31,450 --> 01:50:33,609
And then one day
the doctor came and said,

1420
01:50:33,610 --> 01:50:35,897
"Mr Lauda,
may I offer a piece of advice?"

1421
01:50:36,010 --> 01:50:39,769
"Stop thinking of it as a curse to
have been given an enemy in life."

1422
01:50:39,770 --> 01:50:42,009
"It can be a blessing, too."

1423
01:50:42,010 --> 01:50:44,775
"A wise man gets more from his enemies
than a fool from his friends."

1424
01:50:45,410 --> 01:50:47,697
And you know what? He was right.

1425
01:50:50,290 --> 01:50:54,089
Look at us. We were both
a pair of kids when we met.

1426
01:50:54,090 --> 01:50:55,929
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1427
01:50:55,930 --> 01:50:57,773
Disowned by our families.

1428
01:50:57,890 --> 01:50:59,255
Headed nowhere.

1429
01:51:00,370 --> 01:51:02,729
And now we're both
champions of the world.

1430
01:51:02,730 --> 01:51:04,141
It was not bad, huh?

1431
01:51:05,210 --> 01:51:07,209
No, it's not bad.

1432
01:51:07,210 --> 01:51:10,771
So, don't let me down now.
I need you busting my balls.

1433
01:51:11,210 --> 01:51:13,975
- Get back to work.
- I will, Niki, I will.

1434
01:51:14,730 --> 01:51:16,778
But I intend to enjoy myself first.

1435
01:51:17,130 --> 01:51:19,451
Some of life needs to be for pleasure.

1436
01:51:19,570 --> 01:51:22,969
What's the point of having
a million cups and medals and planes

1437
01:51:22,970 --> 01:51:25,132
if you don't have any fun?

1438
01:51:25,930 --> 01:51:27,659
How is that winning?

1439
01:51:28,730 --> 01:51:31,461
- James!
- We're gonna leave without you!

1440
01:51:31,970 --> 01:51:33,415
James!

1441
01:51:37,250 --> 01:51:38,661
I'll see you on race day, champ.

1442
01:51:40,410 --> 01:51:42,572
You will... champ.

1443
01:51:45,090 --> 01:51:46,854
You look good, Niki.

1444
01:51:47,410 --> 01:51:50,300
The only guy to have his face burnt off
and it be an improvement.

1445
01:51:57,130 --> 01:51:59,249
<i>Of course,
he didn't listen to me.</i>

1446
01:51:59,250 --> 01:52:00,769
<i>For James,</i>

1447
01:52:00,770 --> 01:52:02,969
<i>one world title was enough.</i>

1448
01:52:02,970 --> 01:52:04,489
<i>He had proved</i>

1449
01:52:04,490 --> 01:52:07,849
<i>what he needed to prove, to himself</i>

1450
01:52:07,850 --> 01:52:10,137
<i>and anyone who doubted him.</i>

1451
01:52:10,970 --> 01:52:12,859
<i>And two years later he retired.</i>

1452
01:52:13,130 --> 01:52:16,771
<i>When I saw him next in London
seven years later,</i>

1453
01:52:16,890 --> 01:52:19,018
<i>me as champion again,</i>

1454
01:52:19,130 --> 01:52:21,089
<i>him as broadcaster,</i>

1455
01:52:21,090 --> 01:52:25,493
<i>he was barefoot
on a bicycle with a flat tyre.</i>

1456
01:52:25,610 --> 01:52:28,454
<i>Still living each day like his last.</i>

1457
01:52:30,210 --> 01:52:31,700
<i>When I heard he'd died,</i>

1458
01:52:31,810 --> 01:52:34,177
<i>aged 45, of a heart attack,</i>

1459
01:52:34,290 --> 01:52:35,815
<i>I wasn't surprised.</i>

1460
01:52:36,810 --> 01:52:38,699
<i>I was just sad.</i>

1461
01:52:40,050 --> 01:52:41,969
<i>People always think of us as rivals,</i>

1462
01:52:41,970 --> 01:52:45,577
<i>but he was among the very few I liked,</i>

1463
01:52:46,890 --> 01:52:49,860
<i>and even fewer that I respected.</i>

1464
01:52:53,010 --> 01:52:55,741
<i>He remains the only person I envied.</i>

1465
